</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,458]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,271,297]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species, which is widespread in peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[900,960,272,298]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">India</collectingCountry>
along the Western Ghats in the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,289,312,338]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Tamil Nadu</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[345,426,312,338]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">Kerala</collectingRegion>
, can be distinguished by the long basal processes of the aedeagal shaft. Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2007" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montanus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">P.montanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2007" box="[248,401,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosus">
<emphasis box="[248,401,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">P. bispinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are closely related to each other compared to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viraktamath &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2007" box="[940,1090,352,377]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pythamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biramosus">
<emphasis box="[940,1090,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="57">P. biramosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The female seventh sternum illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Datta, B." box="[314,458,392,418]" pageId="6" pageNumber="57" pagination="102 - 108" refId="ref4313" refString="Datta, B. 1972. On Indian Cicadellidae (Homoptera) - VI. Zoologischer Anzeinger, Leipzig, 189, 102 - 108." type="journal article" year="1972">Datta (1972</bibRefCitation>
, Plate 5 E) belongs to this species as it has a fairly large median lobe on the hind margin of the female seventh sternite.
</paragraph>
